The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Jaipur, April 16 (PTI): A man committed suicide by consuming poison after killing his son and daughter. Soon after, his brother-in-law was crushed to death in an accident while he was rushing to the spot on hearing the news. 

 Shobhalal, a schoolteacher, pushed Mukul, 5, and Divya, 7, into a well, police said. He left behind a suicide note saying personal tension and failure in a competitive examination were the reasons behind the extreme step. 

 Madurai (PTI): Residents of Thenur, upset with district officials for not taking action against a former panchayat chief, submitted their grievances on a flexi-board. One resident tried to display the board in public before submitting it to the collector, following which police seized it from him. 

 Jalandhar (PTI): A boy missing from the Central Reserve Police Force camp here since last month was reunited with his family after the district police found him in Ambala. Anand Kumar, son of a constable working in the camp, had fled from home after he was beaten by his mother, police said.

 Salem (PTI): A nine-member gang that waylaid a group of tourists and robbed them of jewellery, wristwatches and cellphones valued at Rs 1 lakh, were arrested within six hours, police said. The group was returning from Tiruvanamalai temple when the gang intercepted their van.

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A woman in Macheri village in Saharanpur district was allegedly beaten up by her husband and in-laws for not voting for a candidate who her family supported. Imarana is in hospital.

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A court has sentenced four persons to life imprisonment for beating to death a labourer in 2003. The labourer was assaulted as he had demanded money to carry wood in his cart.




